      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your symptoms sound like a typical stomachache, possibly due to gas or menstrual cramps. I recommend taking a couple of ibuprofen, 400 mg every 6-8 hours, to help alleviate the pain. If that doesn't work, you can also take a small dose of codeine, 30-60 mg, but be cautious with the dosage and don't exceed 120 mg per day. Remember, if the pain persists or worsens, it's important to seek medical attention. Rest well and take care of yourself.",
